.TH "vmw_resource_reserve" 9 "vmw_resource_reserve" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_resource_reserve \- Reserve a resource for command submission
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_resource_reserve
.BI "(struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ","
.BI "bool no_backup "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "res" 12
The resource to reserve.
.IP "interruptible" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "no_backup" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function takes the resource off the LRU list and make sure
a backup buffer is present for guest-backed resources. However,
the buffer may not be bound to the resource at this point.
